the overall pattern. Across multiple causes, the District of Columbia, Illinois, 
Wisconsin, and Michigan had the highest contributions to black-white inequality, 
while New York, Massachusetts, and Rhode Island had the lowest contributions and 
have either achieved or are the closest to achieving black-white equality in 
life expectancy.

