(p < 0.001), Right (p < 0.001), and Left Flexion (p < 0.001) whereas significant 
improvements in LHGS (p < 0.01), and right extension (p < 0.05) & left extension 
(p < 0.001) from baseline in Yoga group. Conclusion: IAYT practice showed an 
improvement in TUG, STS, HGS, and Goniometer test, which suggest improved 
muscular strength, flexibility, and functional mobility. CTRI Registration 
Number: http://ctri.nic.in/Clinicaltrials, identifier CTRI/2017/10/010141.

